Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.43,0:01:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, Oka! \NThat's enough for today!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.55,0:01:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.43,0:01:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All-Japan Open's matchups are announced.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.02,0:01:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The opponent you are to face \Nin the initial round is Midorikawa Ranko.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.74,0:01:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, whoever wins \Nyour clash with Midorikawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.74,0:02:04.75,Sign,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa Ranko \NOka Hiromi \NRyuzaki Reika
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.70,0:02:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is to bump immediately into the third seed, \NRyuzaki, in round two.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.71,0:02:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This draw is carved in stone now.{/This decision is based on a strict/unambiguous/irretractable lottery}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.11,0:02:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Originating from chaos,{/decided by chance/accident} \Nthose matchups turned out{/became} quite ironic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.76,0:02:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,True struggle only begins now.{unsure maybe "It'll be a fussy fracas from the very beginning"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.23,0:02:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Though there was no avoiding \Nfacing them sooner or later anyhow.{/though sooner or later you would have become rivals/opponents in competition anyway}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.70,0:02:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFEFDFF&\bord11\blur11\3c&HFFA958&\t(0,1000,\bord0\blur0.4\c&HF2E7E9&\3c&HF1AF5E&)\fnGabriola\fs90\pos(320,350)}Episode 12\N\N\N{\fs110}Bullet Serve: Revival!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.76,0:02:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa! \NJust when did you return?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.77,0:02:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night. I thought to give you a call, \Nbut figured it was too late already.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.77,0:02:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's continue{/come} inside. \NI was just about to have a tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.66,0:02:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine here. \NI only stopped by for a moment,{/I didn't plan to linger anyway}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.43,0:02:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to{/I thought I'd} give you this little thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.59,0:02:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Souvenir for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.72,0:03:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What?{/Is this...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.43,0:03:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Meet the ball I was using during practices in Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.55,0:03:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't mind, \Nit would be nice to show this ball to Hiromi too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.12,0:03:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no fun{/Because it would be pityful/unfair} in her bumping into me \Nunaware{/knowing nothing} of my new tricks{added}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.35,0:03:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I got you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.31,0:03:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, see you in round two. \NI'll be looking forward to it. Truly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.08,0:03:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We only have three days left{guess - taigai}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.47,0:03:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Catching a cold in such a rain \Nwould be a very stupid move now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.04,0:03:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You're exempted from practice today. \NReturn home and make sure to rest well.{/gain enough strength for later}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.51,0:03:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.47,0:03:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, before I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.63,0:03:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki suggested you could use this.{guess, Lit is "special thing to use from Ryuzaki" or idk, maybe "a used thing from Ryuzaki"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.71,0:03:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.45,0:03:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the ball Midorikawa used for trainings \Nduring her trip to Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.22,0:03:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to take it with hand, Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.94,0:03:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.33,0:03:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.38,0:04:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It weighs six ounces. A special purpose ball, \Nthrice as heavy as your usual ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.41,0:04:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ranko's bullet serve is even more formidable now, \Nhaving used this ball for {special }practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.94,0:04:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If she managed to grow accustomed to hitting this ball{/freely}, \Nher serve has received a truly horrifying power-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.56,0:04:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,'Tis me - Ranko.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.97,0:04:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Jin...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.31,0:04:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No hard feelings{/didn't mean to offend/don't get mad/I don't mean to sound arrogant(other meaning)}, but I'm going to defeat Oka. \NI'm confident I will{/I have self-confidence/a hunch}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.46,0:04:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, after that, Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.61,0:04:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That said, an intention is still just an intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.47,0:04:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I explored a new place by myself, \Ndid what I have never done, then returned.{Lit: Alone, I went to a place I don't know, did what had to be done and came back - I don't know what she implies by that so I can to conjure a new meaning, less vague and sounding less out of blue because how the fuck is this connected to adjacent lines}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.79,0:04:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Jin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.87,0:04:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Tennis can be a truly wonderful thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.12,0:05:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi, I hope you're in high spirits,{/are you doing well?} \Nbecause I brought along{guess - jinchunihai} some shortcakes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.64,0:05:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't like it? \NIt's from Rol{/n}and{'s shop} in front of station you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.07,0:05:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.13,0:05:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't say! \NWhy won't you show some more relish then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.03,0:05:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Relish-relish!{/I relish it, I relish/It's delicious-delicious; maybe make this "relish-smellish" thought it does not fit Hiromi's character whatsoever}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.75,0:05:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's the start of rainy season already?{/I wonder if ... starts early this year}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.11,0:05:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If it goes on pouring like that, \Nyou imagine they'll postpone the tournament?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.57,0:05:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I should go there after all. If I hit it \Nagainst the wall in the park, I can practice{/do it} by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.22,0:05:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.16,0:05:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You should stop after all! \NHaven't you had plenty{/enough} of practice up to this point?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.86,0:05:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Even this brute Coach Katsura \Nordered you to get well-rested today!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.17,0:05:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I may have had enough, \Nyet some did twice...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.34,0:06:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They did three or even four times{she actually says 4 times and 6 times respectively but that's how Japanese use this construction, not english} \Nmore than what I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.19,0:06:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover... Moreover, there might as well be someone \Nwho did even more than that!{/But there's no telling if there's no person who ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.29,0:06:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Midorikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.68,0:06:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As well as Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.75,0:06:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.23,0:06:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you alright, Hiromi? \NWhat happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.63,0:06:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Intact{/undamaged/OK}. It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.21,0:06:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.92,0:06:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly - isn't she astonishing? \NHaving practiced with a ball like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.99,0:06:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely fantastic. \NWhat a fantastic person Midorikawa is!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.73,0:06:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Maki, hold it for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.95,0:07:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one of those nights, Munakata, \Nwhen I can drink sake happily.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.76,0:07:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I so happy about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.05,0:07:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, why shouldn't I be happy?{/Just happy somewhy, that's it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.14,0:07:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me think. \NWell, for instance, about those matchups.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.73,0:07:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The very first match is Oka vs. Midorikawa, \Nthen the last man standing{/whoever wins/survives} fights Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.96,0:07:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Those matchups cut straight to the chase,{/are truly short-tempered/have some guts} \Njust like you used to{/they are so much like you/it's as if you rigged it}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.99,0:07:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No use denying{/don't try to conceal it} - it must have been you \Nwho arranged{/rigged} the whole thing{ this way} from your next life{/afterlife; in buddgism, death is rebirth so I'm playing along}{, I realized it}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.74,0:07:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it the moment \Nthose matchups were posted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.83,0:07:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, I'd do the same myself.{Lit: I came here with you, you know - no clue what he means, had to conjecture}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.50,0:07:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess, we still have you. \NThat Munakata Jin guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.17,0:07:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,still looking closely after each one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.80,0:07:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good, \NI may have overdrunk a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.27,0:07:58.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(3000,1000)}January 15th \NDeparture for US \NOka, aim for the ace!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.37,0:08:24.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{Sponsored by Japanese Tennis Association}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.36,0:08:31.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,Colosseum "Shonan"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.37,0:08:38.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,All-Japan's Open Tennis Tournament
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.91,0:08:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.23,0:09:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jin, light more sparklers! \NMore fireworks!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.55,0:09:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the last one, Ranko.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.83,0:09:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I want more!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.99,0:09:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, tomorrow, I'll buy a whole lot more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.15,0:09:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No-no-no! \NNow or never!{/I don't want later/not now}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.48,0:09:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Jin, how lovely{/beautiful}! \NRight? Lovely, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.96,0:09:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, charming...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.89,0:09:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It must have been you who summoned{/Surely, it was Jin who called} them here! \NAll of them, for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.03,0:09:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ranko, I'm not some kind of magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.62,0:09:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Jin can do something like that. \NJin can do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.87,0:09:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you have a good sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.41,0:09:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember distinctly \None dream that I saw at dawn.{more like "I spent the dawn watching dreams entirely" but that makes little sense: how do you know you did it through dawn only?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.87,0:10:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been seeing this dream for some time now.{rather "in this place, I always see that dream"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.38,0:10:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.25,0:10:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.15,0:10:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.51,0:10:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You've finally been{/When were you} discharged from hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.03,0:10:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're having such an important match, \NI can't afford getting hospitalized!{/don't have time for .../how can I be hospitalized/how can I waste time in hospital/no hospital walls can stop me}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.59,0:10:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Meeting you \Nwas the grandest blessing of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.03,0:10:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This train... \NWhere is it heading{/going} to?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.63,0:10:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Know knows...{/I wonder}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.53,0:10:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But... But we'll be together on it{added}, right? \NTogether with Coach, always...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.21,0:10:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.05,0:10:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You aren't going somewhere else now{/already}, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.50,0:10:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Just where do you imagine I can go now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.86,0:10:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect! That's perfect!{/got it/you did it/it's a promise}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.75,0:10:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Maki, you heard it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.52,0:10:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Distinctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.48,0:10:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Coach gave you an irrevocable promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.80,0:10:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't ever again go somewhere else!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.57,0:11:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\t(2500,2750,\shad4\c&H132568&\3c&H0234FF&\4c&H1645EA&)}Perfect! Just perfect!{/I'm so glad!}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.62,0:11:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, let's go. It's time!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.90,0:11:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.75,0:11:19.32,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(1400,500)}All-Japan's Open Tennis Tournament
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.71,0:11:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The best of three set match.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.63,0:11:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa vs. Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.13,0:11:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa's service. Play!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.82,0:11:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,15-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.55,0:12:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,30-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.52,0:12:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm confident I'll win, Jin. Certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.68,0:12:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A thousand daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.51,0:12:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This red{added} ball, even though it weighs 180 gram, \NI kept hitting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.46,0:12:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All alone, in Australian wilderness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.30,0:12:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When no one was there,{/I didn't have anyone}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.59,0:12:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,"Keep it up. Keep it all up!" -
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.19,0:12:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I could hear you cheering for me, Jin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.93,0:12:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Except for your voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.83,0:12:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,there was nothing else in that wasteland.{she uses another term for wilderness/desert/heath totally replaceable with previous one}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.86,0:13:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I will defeat Oka Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.76,0:13:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I will defeat Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.87,0:13:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.41,0:13:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,my own, brand new tennis will be born \Nfrom the ruins{/from now on}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.12,0:13:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I want people to say, \N"That's what you'd expect from Munakata Jin's sister!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.04,0:13:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I will make them say so,{/I'll do it} Jin!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.47,0:13:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,40-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.31,0:13:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as expected. Australia gave her a first-class power-up \Nfor her bullet serve.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.02,0:13:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it look on Oka's side{/What about Oka's shape/How is Oka looking}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.88,0:13:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In order.{all right}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.90,0:13:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels like she's just getting started.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.89,0:13:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She has a leeway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.15,0:13:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That said, she is actually starting to sweat. \NBut it's hot today after all{had he said it in some more ambiguous way, I'd suggest he means "the battle is becoming more intense, but here it's explicitly "temperature is rising"}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.60,0:14:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Game!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.46,0:14:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Game count: 1-0, Midorikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.95,0:14:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A love-game... \NOka never managed to return that serve even once.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.71,0:14:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Court change.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.68,0:14:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Astonishing{/impressive}. \NI'm actually stupefied{/was totally surprised}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.46,0:14:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Wish I could ever hit a serve like that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.08,0:14:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.50,0:14:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Accept my thanks.{/I'm grateful}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.03,0:14:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Had Coach not been there \Nto teach me all those things about tennis,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.47,0:14:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,playing on this court today, \Nagainst an amazing player such as Midorikawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.76,0:14:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have ever experienced{/known} all of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.51,0:14:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,For the moment, though still shivering a bit, \NI flare up with every ball{added}!{maybe "I throbble a little then flame up"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.53,0:15:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,15-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.07,0:15:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.92,0:15:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,15-All.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.20,0:15:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever I do, \NI can't enforce my own service game{I've been reading tennis rules for 10 minutes now both in EN and in JP and I'm still unsure as to what they refer to as service game; I would assume everyone is as ignoramus in tennis rules as I am ¯\_(ツ)_/¯} over her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.03,0:15:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if Midorikawa aces every single ball \Nin her own service-game,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.02,0:15:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I will still be able \Nto make it to a tie-break somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.80,0:16:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If I manage that, sooner or later, who knows, \Nmaybe I'll find a way to undermine{/resist/break through/disrupt} the bullet serve.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.93,0:16:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if I never find a way, \NI would at least be contented with losing in a close match!{/just giving her a run for her money is good enough too}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.86,0:16:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,30-15.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.97,0:16:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The men's first round that only starts tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.25,0:16:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is completely overshadowed already \Nby this women's match alone.{/this women's match is uncomparable in intensity to any of tomorrow men's round 1 matches}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.67,0:16:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! 40-15!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.63,0:17:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Game: Oka. \NGame count: 1-All.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.07,0:17:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, mom... Well, if you want some, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.89,0:17:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They exchange hits pretty evenly.{/It is actually a pretty close match} \NNo, rather, if we talk{guess} speed, Oka has the upper hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.23,0:17:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the only obstacle \Nis Midorikawa's serve.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.90,0:17:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,For Oka, in order to win this match, \Nit is imperative
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.40,0:17:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to eventually find a way \Nto undermine{/break through} that knockout{/severe} serve.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.59,0:17:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,My wrist warmed up{it's rather "I must wrap my wrist around tightly" but it's either a case of engrish for you can't wrap a wrist or just my poor hearing and it may be "warm up as well"} properly. \NI'm ready{guess} to receive in{guess: kurashi} whatever direction{/left and right, up and down; half-guess, the best I could come up with is 縦横自} you hit it{the tone suggests she would rather hit it herself but I hate this sentence and can't be bothered with it any longer}!{for some reason both my fr to ru and Johnny's versions had "weight" and "legs" in it, but I can't hear any; perhaps that was just a "fuck-off" way out for original french translator though "using legs and weight to receive bullet serve" would actually make sense here}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.93,0:17:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,15-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.39,0:18:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa is amazing! If you include previous games, \Nit's her fifth consecutive service-ace!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.39,0:18:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,While Oka couldn't handle a single receive yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.46,0:18:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the first time I see a girl \Nwielding such a mighty serve.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.19,0:18:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Bullet serve of Kaga's Lady Orchid. \NHaven't you heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.99,0:18:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She was renowned since her days as a junior.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.85,0:18:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do I have a feeling \Nit's due to{/Can it be because ... are a little late} my stepping-in timings being a bit tardy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.31,0:18:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,One...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.11,0:18:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Two...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.36,0:18:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.87,0:19:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No use... Whatever I do, \NI can't undermine that serve.{/this serve seems invincible}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.05,0:19:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's turning ugly. \NOka dropped a game of her own serving.{/her own game/dropped a serve}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.57,0:19:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Nailed it again! \NMidorikawa just scored her 16th{unclear} service ace in a row!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.25,0:19:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Dead end!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.94,0:19:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't win it. This one match...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.43,0:19:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If you excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.60,0:19:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.79,0:19:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi's gonna{guess} lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.00,0:19:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Gonna lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.36,0:19:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. \NI thought there might{/I was just wondering if there's} be something I could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.68,0:20:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the opponent is Midorikawa, \Nso whoever wins is still a part of our family anyhow.{/is probably to our favor/whoever wins, they are like relatives/sworn sisters - LIT/I wouln't mind it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.99,0:20:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm sitting right next to Hiromi's parents, \Nwhom I brought along.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.62,0:20:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is she, Jin? \NHey, tell me,{/who in the world} who is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.61,0:20:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this Oka Hiromi girl? \NJin, what is this girl to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.13,0:20:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought you're finally back to the tennis world, day in and day out, it's just Oka, Oka, nothing but Oka!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.80,0:20:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Like she is some sweetheart{/beloved one} of yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.59,0:20:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe she {\i1}is{\i0} my sweetheart. \NHow do you know?{/A beloved one? That's not impossible}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.71,0:20:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Having one always on your mind,{/worrying about someone,} \Nwanting them to tell you everything about themselves{unsure maybe it's "to want to tell them everything about yourself"}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.08,0:20:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Accepting in entirety \Nboth everything good and bad about them...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.15,0:20:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Being forgiving. But above all, making every effort \Nto share the same path that lies ahead of them -
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.15,0:20:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,if that translates to holding her as my sweetheart, \Nthen it's quite possible.{/then I really don't know what to make of it/then who knows}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.95,0:20:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Come over, Ranko.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.51,0:20:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The nightscape is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.99,0:20:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I refuse{ [to believe] - is it clear enough}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.45,0:20:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.08,0:20:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I refuse! Refuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.55,0:21:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Is she really that important to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.69,0:21:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.48,0:21:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.27,0:21:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly is still watching{, you know}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.63,0:21:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And perhaps, Jin does too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.83,0:23:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Aikawa Maki here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.04,0:23:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's here at last! \NThe grand showdown with Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.18,0:23:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm happy with any outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.98,0:23:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, with all the different things that happened since, \Nwe have Hiromi standing on the court once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.50,0:23:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough to dispel all my worries!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.70,0:23:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind her back, Hiromi has Todo and friends, \Nand Coach Katsura,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.24,0:23:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as Coach Munakata, \Nalways by her side!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.86,0:23:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time: I'm Sure... He's Watching.
